This paper is likely to belong to the Computer Vision (cs.CV) sub-category as it deals with 3D object detection, semantic and part segmentation, and scene segmentation. It also involves deep learning, which is a common topic in the Machine Learning (cs.LG) sub-category. The use of convolutional neural networks (CNNs) suggests that it could also be relevant to the Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category. The paper's focus on improving memory and computation efficiency could place it in the Graphics (cs.GR) sub-category, while its application to 3D object detection could also make it relevant to the Robotics (cs.RO) sub-category.
